					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I feel like there's not really a hook, nothing to make me go &quot;That was a good read&quot;. The last addendum tries, but I sincerely don't get what's supposed to be surprising or interesting about it, especially when you outright state that it can eat &quot;anything deemed 'man-made', including[&#8230;] humans themselves&quot;. Besides that, the concept is too busy to digest in such a short article, and the lazy containment procedures rub me the wrong way.</p> 
				 	]]>
